-    CHECK_LT(ref_count_, INT_MAX);
-    ++ref_count_;
+    CHECK_GT(ref_count_+inc, 0);

body:
Assuming ref_count and inc are both non-negative, this CHECK_GT will only fail in the event of signed overflow which is undefined behavior so this CHECK can't be relied upon. How about replacing it with:

CHECK_GT(inc, 0);
CHECK_LT(ref_count_, INT_MAX - inc + 1);

